{{Infobox venue | name = 013 | nickname = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | fullname = | former names = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = Tilburg poppodium 013.jpg | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = 013 in Tilburg | pushpin_map = Netherlands North Brabant | pushpin_mapsize = 250px | pushpin_map_caption = Location in [[North Brabant]] | pushpin_label_position = | address = | location = Tilburg, the Netherlands | coordinates = {{coord|51|33|31|N|5|05|35|E|region:NL_type:landmark_source:kolossus-nlwiki|display=inline, title}} | type = Music venue | genre = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1998 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | production = | cost = | architect = | builder = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | seating_type = | capacity = 3000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | field_shape = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | publictransit = }}
'''013''' is a music venue in [[Tilburg]], the [[Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.brabantsdagblad.nl/algemeen/kunst/4938323/HollandBelgie-op-podium-van-013.ece | title=Holland-België op podium van 013 | work=[[Brabants Dagblad]] | date=May 8, 2009 | accessdate=July 31, 2011|language=nl}}</ref> The venue opened in 1998 and replaced the ''Noorderligt'', the ''Bat Cave'' and the ''MuziekKantenWinkel''. 013 is the largest popular music venue in the southern Netherlands.
There are two concert halls of which the "Main Stage" (formerly ''Jupiler Zaal'' and ''Dommelsch Zaal'') is the largest, with a capacity of 3,000 attendees. The smaller stage have a capacity of 700 attendees.
The name of the venue is based on the [[area code]] of Tilburg.
In August 2011, the director of 013, Guus van Hove, died of heat exposure in the Californian [[Joshua Tree National Park]], together with his girlfriend.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.webpronews.com/dutch-tourist-guus-van-hove-director-of-013-dead-at-joshua-tree-national-park-2011-08 | title=Dutch Tourist Guus Van Hove, Director of 013, Dead at Joshua Tree National Park | work=WebProNews|author=Josh Wolford | date=2011-08-26 | accessdate=2011-08-26}}</ref><ref>{{nl icon}} [https://web.archive.org/web/20110828233435/http://www.013.nl/blog/1000_onze_geliefde_directeur_overleden Onze geliefde directeur overleden], 013 blog, 2011-08-24 (archive)</ref> Van Hove had told friends he planned to visit the site of U2's [[The Joshua Tree#Packaging and title|The Joshua Tree]] album cover, which they falsely assumed to be near the location where they died.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://blogs.laweekly.com/informer/2011/08/guus_van_hove_joshua_tree_u2.php|title=Guus Van Hove, Dutch Music Man Who Died in Joshua Tree, May Have Been Searching for Site of U2's Album Cover|author=Simone Wilson|work=[[LA Weekly]]|date=2011-08-26|accessdate=2011-08-26}}</ref>
013 hosts the bigger acts at the annual music festivals [[Roadburn]] ([[stoner rock]] festival), [[Incubate (festival)|Incubate]] Festival and [[Neurotic Deathfest]].
