The '''6th Separate Tank Brigade''' is a formation of the [[Russian Ground Forces]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://voinskayachast.net/suhoputnie-voyska/tankovie/vch54096|title=Войсковая часть 54096 (6 отбр) поселок Мулино|website=voinskayachast.net|access-date=2016-08-18}}</ref> In 2014–2015 the brigade fought in the [[War in Donbass|War in Donbas]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Sutyagin|first=Igor|date=March 2015|title=RUSI Briefing Paper: Russian Forces in Ukraine|url=https://rusi.org/sites/default/files/201503_bp_russian_forces_in_ukraine.pdf|journal=|publisher=[[Royal United Services Institute]]|volume=|issue=|page=3|doi=|pmid=|access-date=6 April 2016|via=}}</ref>

== History ==
The brigade was formed in June 2009 as part of the [[20th Guards Army]] in [[Mulino (settlement), Nizhny Novgorod Oblast|Mulino]] from the 100th Tank Regiment. The 100th Tank Regiment was originally formed as the [[100th Tank Brigade (Soviet Union)|100th Tank Brigade]] in 1942. For its actions during [[World War II]], the brigade was awarded the [[Order of the Red Banner]], the [[Order of Kutuzov]] 2nd class, and the honorific "Czestochowa".<ref name=":0" /> In 1945 the brigade, part of the [[31st Tank Corps (Soviet Union)|31st Tank Corps]], became the 100th Tank Regiment as part of a reorganization of the Soviet Tank Troops. At the same time the corps became the 31st Tank Division. The regiment was based in [[Khmelnytskyi, Ukraine|Khmelnitsky]]. The regiment fought in [[Operation Danube]], the suppression of the [[Prague Spring]]. After the end of the operation the regiment stayed in Czechoslovakia with the division and was based at [[Frenštát pod Radhoštěm]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ww2.dk/new/army/td/31td.htm|title=31st Tank Division|last=Holm|first=Michael|date=|website=www.ww2.dk|publisher=|access-date=2016-08-19}}</ref> In early 1990 the regiment withdrew to [[Dzerzhinsk, Russia|Dzerzhinsk]].<ref name=":0" />

In August 2014 the brigade's units fought in the [[Battle of Ilovaisk]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bellingcat.com/news/uk-and-europe/2015/09/22/russias-6th-tank-brigade/|title=Russia's 6th Tank Brigade: The Dead, the Captured, and the Destroyed Tanks (Pt. 1) – bellingcat|date=2015-09-22|language=en-US|access-date=2016-08-18}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bellingcat.com/news/uk-and-europe/2015/09/29/russias-6th-tank-brigade-pt-2/|title=Russia's 6th Tank Brigade: The Dead, the Captured, and the Destroyed Tanks (Pt. 2) – bellingcat|date=2015-09-29|language=en-US|access-date=2016-08-18}}</ref> On 26 August, during a fight near Ahronomichne village, a [[T-72B3]] tank of the 1st Company of the brigade's 3rd Battalion was captured by troops of the Ukrainian [[51st Guards Mechanized Brigade (Ukraine)|51st Mechanized Brigade]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://censor.net.ua/resonance/349305/polkovnik_kovalskiyi_rossiyiskiyi_t72b3_my_zahvatili_neojidanno_dlya_samih_sebya_dlya_bolshinstva_eto|title=ПОЛКОВНИК КОВАЛЬСКИЙ: "РОССИЙСКИЙ Т-72Б3 МЫ ЗАХВАТИЛИ НЕОЖИДАННО ДЛЯ САМИХ СЕБЯ - ДЛЯ БОЛЬШИНСТВА ЭТО БЫЛ ПЕРВЫЙ БОЙ"|last=Цензор.НЕТ|newspaper=Цензор.НЕТ|language=ru-RU|access-date=2016-10-31}}</ref> During the Ukrainian forces' withdrawal from Ilovaisk on 29 August, [[Donbas Battalion]] fighters were able to seize and destroy another two brigade T-72B3 tanks near Chervonosilske village,<ref name="donbasT72">{{Citation|last=Elena Finogina|title="Donbas" Battalion had hit Russian T72 tank in Chervonosilske village 29.08.2014|date=2015-07-07|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-oAi_G922g4|accessdate=2016-10-31}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|last=Tatyana Zarovnaja|title=Captured by Ukrainians Russian tank|date=2014-10-29|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i1-U72O751U|accessdate=2016-10-31}}</ref> capturing two prisoners: Ivan Badanin and Eugen Chernov,<ref name=":1" /> as well as some paratroopers of the [[31st Guards Air Assault Brigade|31st Air Assault Brigade]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://informnapalm.org/en/internet-users-have-identified-russian-soldiers-captured-near-ilovaisk/|title=Internet Users Have Identified Russian Soldiers Captured Near Ilovaisk - InformNapalm.org (English)|date=2015-03-27|newspaper=InformNapalm.org (English)|language=en-US|access-date=2016-12-09}}</ref>

In November 2014 the brigade became part of the [[1st Guards Tank Army (Soviet Union)|1st Guards Tank Army.]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/russian/russia/2015/06/150602_russia_tank_army|title=Россия негласно создала гвардейскую танковую армию|last=|first=|date=2 June 2015|work=BBC|language=Russian|trans-title=Russia secretly created Guards Tank Army|access-date=19 August 2016|via=}}</ref> In February 2015 the brigade's units fought in [[Battle of Debaltseve]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://citeam.org/putin-shoygu-debaltseve/|title=Министр обороны РФ наградил солдат часами за Дебальцево — Conflict Intelligence Team|website=citeam.org|access-date=2016-08-18}}</ref>

