{{Politics of the Democratic Republic of the Congo}}
The '''[[Court of Cassation]]''' ({{Lang-fr|1=Cour de cassation}}) is the main court of last resort in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]]. It has its seat in the Kinshasa Palace of Justice.

The Court judges final appeals with respect to the "normal" system of justice, excluding cases of administrative justice, which go before the ''Conseil d'État''.

