{{Politics of Congo (Brazzaville)}}
The '''[[Republic of the Congo]]''' elects on national level a [[head of state]] - the [[president]] -  and a [[legislature]]. The president is elected by the people. The '''[[Parliament of the Republic of Congo|Parliament]]''' (''Parlement'') has [[bicameralism|two chambers]]. The '''[[National Assembly of the Republic of Congo|National Assembly]]''' (''Assemblée Nationale'') has 153 members, for a five-year term in single-seat [[constituency|constituencies]]. The '''[[Senate of the Republic of Congo|Senate]]''' (''Sénat'') has 66 members, elected for a six-year term by district, local and regional councils. The Republic of Congo is a [[one party dominant state]] with the [[Congolese Labour Party]] in power. [[Opposition (politics)|Opposition]] [[political parties|parties]] are allowed, but are widely considered to have no real chance of gaining power.

Elections are governed by [[Election law of the Republic of the Congo|Congo's election law]], most recently modified in 2016.

