{{Infobox Cheese | name = Hushållsost | image = | othernames = Household cheese | country = [[Sweden]] | regiontown = | Nutritional Information= per 100g: 280 calories, 22 g protein, 880 mg calcium | region = | town = | source = [[Cow]]s | pasteurised = Yes | texture = Semi-hard | fat = | protein = | dimensions = | weight = | aging = 60 days | certification = | }} '''''Hushållsost''''' ("household cheese") is a brand made of [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[cattle|cows]]'-[[milk]] [[cheese]]. It is a semi-hard cheese, with small granular holes, and is made from whole milk, which gives it a 26 percent fat content. There is also a version with less fat labeled "17% fetthalt". ''Hushållsost'' is produced in cylinders weighing {{convert|1|to|2|kg|abbr=on}} each, which are today wrapped in plastic film before being aged around 60 days on average. The taste is described as mild yet somewhat sour. The cheese was traditionally produced on farms; the name ''hushållsost'' is found in print at least as early as 1898. It is closely related to [[Port-Salut cheese]].
Consumed at a rate of 15 thousand tonnes a year, ''hushållsost'' is the most popular cheese in Sweden.<ref name="svmjolk">{{cite web | url=http://www.svenskmjolk.se/Mjolk-smor-och-ost/Vara-varumarken/Hushallsost--var-mest-kopta-ost/ | title=Hushållsost – vår mest köpta ost | accessdate=2011-02-11 | author=Larsson, Joakim | work=Svensk mjölk}}</ref> It has [[Protected designation of origin|TSG]] Status.<ref name="DOOREU">[http://ec.europa.eu/agriculture/quality/door/registeredName.html?denominationId=353 EU Profile - Hushållsost] (accessed 07/06/2009)</ref>
