{{Infobox Ethnic group |group = Turks in Liechtenstein |image = |caption = |popplace = {{Flatlist| * [[Vaduz]] * [[Schaan]] * [[Triesen]] }} |langs = [[Turkish language|Turkish]] |rels = [[Islam]] |population=894<ref group=note>This does not include Turks with Liechtensteinian nationality</ref><ref>{{Harvnb|Fürstentum Liechtenstein|2007|loc=6}}.</ref>}}
'''Turks in Liechtenstein''' ({{lang-de|Türken in Liechtenstein}} {{lang-tr|Lihtenştayn Türkleri}}) consist of both [[Turkish people]] who live in [[Liechtenstein]] but were born elsewhere, as well as citizens of Liechtenstein with Turkish roots (meaning origins in [[Turkey]], the island of [[Cyprus]], or communities of the [[Turkish diaspora]]). Presently, 894 Turkish citizens live in Liechtenstein (this does not include Turks with Liechtensteinian nationality), accounting for 3% of the total population of the country.<ref>{{Harvnb|Fürstentum Liechtenstein|2007|loc=6-7}}.</ref> Turks are the fifth-largest group of foreigners in Liechtenstein, behind Swiss, Austrians, Italians, and Germans.<ref>{{Harvnb|Fürstentum Liechtenstein|2007|loc=7}}.</ref> As of 2007, 296 Turkish citizens work in Liechtenstein.<ref>{{Harvnb|Fürstentum Liechtenstein|2007|loc=12}}.</ref>
