'''Äkräs''' (also ''Ägröi'', ''Egres'') was the [[deity|god]] of [[fertility]] in the [[Finnish mythology]]. He was also the god of [[turnip]] and the protector of [[bean]]s, [[pea]]s, [[cabbage]], [[flax]], and [[hemp]]. In [[Karelia]] he was called '''Pyhä Äkräs''' (Holy Äkräs).

